(2) Direct the Commander-in-Chief, United Nations Command (CINCUNC) to increase immediately the scale of
                    military operations in the Korean campaign to the maximum consistent with the
                    capabilities and security of the forces now available or made available;

(4) Support a vigorous campaign of covert operations designed: (a)
To aid effectively anti-Communist guerrilla forces in Communist China and Korea; and (b)
To interfere with and disrupt enemy lines of communications;

(6) Expedite the development and equipment of additional dependable ROK military units, as rapidly as possible, with a
                    view to their assuming an increasing responsibility for the defense of
                    Korea;
